cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically real-time object detection on mobile platforms. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a new lightweight two-stage detector, which involves designing a new backbone and exploiting efficient RPN and detection head designs. This suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the balance between input resolution, backbone, and detection head, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model on benchmarks, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
